                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6374/1023: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-01T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 1, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Your 194, August 29, noon. The Department agrees that you should keep
                    yourself and it currently informed. But, as you have recognized, the Department
                    wishes to keep clear of the negotiations.</p>
                <p>Before taking any action in support of the American interests cable us your views
                    and recommendations so that we may have full information on which to send you
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
